p4
VSaptaswara and Thyagaraya Gana Sabha jointly organised a three-day Sadguru Thyagaraya Jayanthi celebrations at Thyagaraya Gana Sabha Kalasubbrao Kala Vedika recently.The three-day fest paid tribute to saint Thyagaraya by featuring Ghanaraga Pancharathnas.  The Ghanaraga pancharatnas include Kovuru, Narada, Lalgudi, Srirangam,and Thiruvatthiurpancharathnamsall composed and sung by Thyagaraya in praise of their respective Lords.The effort by Saptaswaram is laudable as they organised this special concert. On the occasion renowned Carnatic musician Nookala Chinna Satyanarayana was felicitated with &#8216;Sangeetha Kala Prapoorna&#8217; title.The first day featured Kovurupancharatnamsrendered by Chaganty Maha Lakshmi.Nammi Vachinanuin Kalyani,Korisevimpa Rarein Kharahara Priya,Sundareswaruniin Sankerabharanam,Eevasudhani vantiin Sahana andShambho Mhadevain Panthuvarali was neatly rendered by Mahalakshmi. On the same day Narada Pancharatnas were rendered by Aruna and Padma. The second day followed with Lalgudi Pancharatnas by D. Lakshmi. ThekrithisIesha pahimamin Kalyani,Lalitha sreein Bhairavi,Maheetha Pravrudhain Khambhoji,Ghatineevaniin Thodi,Deva Sreein Madhyamavathi was sung with devotion. The last day featured Thiruvathiurpancharathnamssung by Lalitha Madhav.All the concerts were rendered with devotion by the performers.These concerts were accompanied by Rajashekar on violin and T.P.Bala Subramanyam on the mridangam.
